1
00:00:46,651 --> 00:00:51,072
DYNAMITE KISS

2
00:00:52,532 --> 00:00:55,577
You'll need to share
a room with Ms. Go tonight.

3
00:00:55,660 --> 00:00:56,619
Will you be okay?

4
00:00:56,703 --> 00:01:00,206
Yes, I'll be fine.
We've been friends for over 20 years.

5
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:02,250
That's why it's unsafe…

6
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:04,502
I mean, more uncomfortable.

7
00:01:05,420 --> 00:01:07,422
How about you come out later?

8
00:01:07,505 --> 00:01:09,090
I'll get you another room.

9
00:01:09,883 --> 00:01:12,844
-You don't have to do--
-I don't like it.

10
00:01:25,231 --> 00:01:28,234
If somebody sees me leave,
they could get suspicious.

11
00:01:28,818 --> 00:01:30,361
I have to go with it
even if it's uncomfortable.

12
00:01:30,445 --> 00:01:33,114
Plus, Da-rim is already anxious
about getting caught as it is.

13
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:37,911
Are you always such a perfectionist?

14
00:01:37,994 --> 00:01:40,121
It's something I decided to see through.

15
00:01:41,414 --> 00:01:42,457
So I'm going to try my best.

16
00:01:43,583 --> 00:01:44,584
Let's head back.

17
00:01:46,753 --> 00:01:47,629
Mr. Kim.

18
00:01:52,717 --> 00:01:53,635
In that case,

19
00:01:54,219 --> 00:01:55,511
I also want to try my best.

20
00:01:58,389 --> 00:02:01,643
Because I've just now decided

21
00:02:01,726 --> 00:02:02,560
to see this through.

22
00:02:16,866 --> 00:02:18,701
He's a warm person.

23
00:02:18,785 --> 00:02:21,621
He's warm-hearted and speaks warmly too.

24
00:02:21,704 --> 00:02:22,705
And his face

25
00:02:23,831 --> 00:02:25,458
is just full of so much warmth.

26
00:02:26,209 --> 00:02:27,752
-His wife?
-Ms. Yu?

27
00:02:27,835 --> 00:02:29,963
We're going to step out for a quick chat.
Let's go.

28
00:02:32,882 --> 00:02:35,426
Here you are, Mr. Gong.

29
00:02:37,262 --> 00:02:39,222
Oh, you must've also needed some fresh--

30
00:03:02,745 --> 00:03:04,038
What are you doing?

31
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:08,084
Mr. Gong?

32
00:03:14,632 --> 00:03:15,550
Well, you see…

33
00:03:17,385 --> 00:03:18,219
A flasher.

34
00:03:18,928 --> 00:03:20,805
-Sorry?
-There was a flasher.

35
00:03:20,888 --> 00:03:22,557
Oh, really?

36
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:25,059
Let's spare our eyes and go that way.

37
00:03:25,143 --> 00:03:26,144
Sure, okay.

38
00:03:26,227 --> 00:03:27,353
Let's go.

39
00:03:27,437 --> 00:03:28,646
Okay, okay.

40
00:03:37,572 --> 00:03:38,948
I like you, Mr. Kim.

41
00:03:39,824 --> 00:03:40,783
Sorry?

42
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:42,076
I want to date you.

43
00:03:42,827 --> 00:03:43,703
Oh.

44
00:03:44,287 --> 00:03:47,123
-Well, I--
-You like someone else?

45
00:03:48,374 --> 00:03:51,586
You've been looking at her all day
with such obvious eyes.

46
00:03:51,669 --> 00:03:54,005
Ms. Go Da-rim is the weird one
for not noticing.

47
00:03:55,381 --> 00:03:59,635
But if you've been friends for that long
and still haven't asked her out yet,

48
00:03:59,719 --> 00:04:02,347
doesn't that mean that's the extent
of your feelings for her?

49
00:04:04,307 --> 00:04:05,808
It's that much harder

50
00:04:06,434 --> 00:04:07,852
because we've known each other
for so long.

51
00:04:09,103 --> 00:04:12,190
I don't want to lose the person closest
and most precious to me.

52
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:16,027
You can't ask her out
because you're afraid she'll reject you.

53
00:04:16,694 --> 00:04:18,404
Are you sure that's real love?

54
00:04:18,488 --> 00:04:21,449
I don't think so.
There's nothing simpler than love.

55
00:04:21,532 --> 00:04:25,036
I like you, I want to see you,
and I want you.

56
00:04:25,119 --> 00:04:25,953
That's it.

57
00:04:26,037 --> 00:04:28,247
But I don't have those feelings for you.

58
00:04:28,915 --> 00:04:29,916
It's okay.

59
00:04:29,999 --> 00:04:32,043
If you don't,
I'll just make you have them.

60
00:04:32,877 --> 00:04:34,045
You'd better prepare yourself.

61
00:04:55,691 --> 00:04:58,986
The fresh air is sobering me up.

62
00:05:01,989 --> 00:05:03,699
Should we sit down somewhere for a bit?

63
00:05:04,826 --> 00:05:05,701
Sorry?

64
00:05:07,829 --> 00:05:08,663
Okay.

65
00:05:09,539 --> 00:05:12,333
So what sort of drinking games
do young people play nowadays?

66
00:05:12,417 --> 00:05:14,377
-Drinking games?
-I'm so curious.

67
00:05:14,460 --> 00:05:15,461
I don't play drinking games.

68
00:05:16,337 --> 00:05:18,589
I guess you're not young.

69
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:34,856
Don't these falling petals

70
00:05:36,274 --> 00:05:37,900
remind you of waves?

71
00:05:38,526 --> 00:05:40,445
They're twinkling.

72
00:05:41,529 --> 00:05:42,405
They do.

73
00:05:44,157 --> 00:05:45,491
It reminds me of Jeju Island.

74
00:05:46,075 --> 00:05:47,076
The sea back then

75
00:05:47,577 --> 00:05:50,413
also twinkled like this.

76
00:05:52,498 --> 00:05:53,499
You're right.

77
00:05:54,125 --> 00:05:55,543
It was so pretty.

78
00:06:00,756 --> 00:06:01,757
By any chance,

79
00:06:03,009 --> 00:06:04,719
do you remember what we talked about

80
00:06:06,429 --> 00:06:07,471
back then?

81
00:06:08,347 --> 00:06:10,975
But he's still someone I once loved.

82
00:06:12,018 --> 00:06:13,603
It's a bit disheartening.

83
00:06:14,604 --> 00:06:15,646
You were mistaken.

84
00:06:16,814 --> 00:06:17,648
You mistook it for love.

85
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,944
Does real love even exist to begin with?

86
00:06:23,029 --> 00:06:23,988
I said

87
00:06:25,072 --> 00:06:27,200
love was a mistaken belief.

88
00:06:27,283 --> 00:06:28,826
It definitely exists.

89
00:06:30,203 --> 00:06:31,078
It's just that

90
00:06:31,913 --> 00:06:36,042
there are people who fail to protect it
until the end.

91
00:06:36,584 --> 00:06:37,543
And you said

92
00:06:38,794 --> 00:06:41,130
love definitely exists,

93
00:06:42,381 --> 00:06:43,299
but it's just that…

94
00:06:45,343 --> 00:06:48,221
there are people who fail to protect it
until the end.

95
00:06:50,264 --> 00:06:51,224
I did.

96
00:06:51,849 --> 00:06:54,352
But you know, even after thinking it over,

97
00:06:55,561 --> 00:06:56,896
I still think I'm right.

98
00:06:58,648 --> 00:06:59,649
Why?

99
00:07:01,901 --> 00:07:03,152
That way, if love ends,

100
00:07:04,654 --> 00:07:07,240
you can just think of it
as coming to your senses.

101
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:12,161
If you believe you failed
to protect your love until the end…

102
00:07:16,374 --> 00:07:18,125
you end up blaming yourself.

103
00:07:25,508 --> 00:07:26,926
So don't do such a stupid thing.

104
00:07:28,302 --> 00:07:29,262
Sorry?

105
00:07:29,804 --> 00:07:31,514
Who are you calling stupid?

106
00:07:33,307 --> 00:07:34,433
No, I'm just saying.

107
00:07:36,102 --> 00:07:37,228
What was that?

108
00:08:06,882 --> 00:08:07,967
Hey, Seon-u.

109
00:08:08,676 --> 00:08:10,052
I came out to get some fresh air.

110
00:08:10,636 --> 00:08:11,887
Yeah, I'll be back soon.

111
00:08:12,471 --> 00:08:14,015
Okay, bye.

112
00:08:20,354 --> 00:08:22,064
You can continue drinking inside.

113
00:08:22,148 --> 00:08:22,982
Go on inside.

114
00:08:23,065 --> 00:08:24,108
Good night, everyone.

115
00:08:24,191 --> 00:08:25,401
-You too.
-Good night.

116
00:08:27,612 --> 00:08:29,488
Your hand is so cold, honey.

117
00:08:29,572 --> 00:08:31,866
-You should've asked me to come.
-Right, I should've.

118
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,369
-Let's go together next time.
-Okay.

119
00:08:36,662 --> 00:08:38,497
Room 518. Give me the key.

120
00:08:38,581 --> 00:08:39,874
I don't have it.

121
00:08:39,957 --> 00:08:40,875
You took it earlier.

122
00:08:40,958 --> 00:08:42,126
-I don't have it.
-Is it in here?

123
00:08:45,087 --> 00:08:46,797
-Sorry.
-Seriously?

124
00:08:47,423 --> 00:08:48,507
-Come on.
-Okay.

125
00:08:49,216 --> 00:08:50,134
Careful.

126
00:08:57,975 --> 00:08:58,976
Hold on.

127
00:09:19,914 --> 00:09:23,167
Seriously, what's going on?

128
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,711
What's with you? You look like someone
who desperately needs the bathroom.

129
00:09:25,795 --> 00:09:28,130
Did Ha-yeong head to her room early?

130
00:09:28,214 --> 00:09:30,883
I think so. She said she was tired.

131
00:09:36,597 --> 00:09:39,433
Look at him taking care of his fiancée.

132
00:09:39,517 --> 00:09:40,559
I guess not.

133
00:09:56,117 --> 00:09:57,243
I mean,

134
00:09:57,326 --> 00:10:01,497
a photographer
should have a far more discerning eye.

135
00:10:15,928 --> 00:10:17,471
Seon-u, you can wash up now.

136
00:10:18,764 --> 00:10:20,808
-Oh, okay.
-Go on.

137
00:10:24,562 --> 00:10:26,772
Are you sick? What's that medicine for?

138
00:10:26,856 --> 00:10:28,566
It's stress-induced gastritis, apparently.

139
00:10:29,275 --> 00:10:31,193
I guess I'm not meant to be an actor.

140
00:10:35,865 --> 00:10:36,824
You sure you're okay?

141
00:10:36,907 --> 00:10:37,992
Of course.

142
00:10:40,453 --> 00:10:41,787
Get into bed and get some rest.

143
00:10:42,997 --> 00:10:45,416
What? I don't mind sleeping on the floor.

144
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:49,754
-Rock, paper--
-No need.

145
00:10:49,837 --> 00:10:52,590
We can just share the bed.
It's big enough.

146
00:10:53,299 --> 00:10:54,133
What?

147
00:10:54,216 --> 00:10:56,177
Why not?
We slept together all the time as kids.

148
00:10:57,470 --> 00:10:59,972
Hey, we're not kids anymore.

149
00:11:02,141 --> 00:11:03,309
What's with you?

150
00:11:04,226 --> 00:11:05,311
Fine, forget it.

151
00:11:06,270 --> 00:11:08,981
Oh my, it's so nice and big.

152
00:11:10,024 --> 00:11:11,567
I'll enjoy this bed alone.

153
00:11:17,531 --> 00:11:19,033
Was I okay today?

154
00:11:19,950 --> 00:11:20,910
As your husband?

155
00:11:22,411 --> 00:11:26,123
You saw how everyone was green with envy.

156
00:11:26,749 --> 00:11:27,625
Thanks.

157
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:29,710
It must've been tough acting all day.

158
00:11:31,629 --> 00:11:33,797
-I wasn't acting.
-What?

159
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:37,843
I wasn't acting.

160
00:11:40,012 --> 00:11:41,680
I was just being myself.

161
00:11:42,431 --> 00:11:43,349
Then again,

162
00:11:44,642 --> 00:11:46,727
you were so good to Jun's mom
when you were with her.

163
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:56,612
Sorry, I just meant to say

164
00:11:56,695 --> 00:12:00,032
something along the lines
of you being excellent husband material.

165
00:12:01,325 --> 00:12:03,035
-Da-rim.
-Yeah?

166
00:12:07,373 --> 00:12:08,707
What do you think of me

167
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:11,043
as a man and not as a husband?

168
00:12:11,126 --> 00:12:12,378
What?

169
00:12:16,298 --> 00:12:17,800
What do you think of me

170
00:12:19,176 --> 00:12:20,177
as a man?

171
00:12:37,528 --> 00:12:38,862
No way.

172
00:12:38,946 --> 00:12:41,365
You have a crush on someone, don't you?
Who is it? Tell me right now.

173
00:12:41,448 --> 00:12:43,033
Don't tell me it's Ms. Yu!

174
00:12:45,661 --> 00:12:46,662
No, it's not like that.

175
00:12:46,745 --> 00:12:47,746
Why not?

176
00:12:47,830 --> 00:12:49,915
I can totally see
how you'd be attracted to her.

177
00:12:49,999 --> 00:12:52,835
-You should go for it!
-I said it's not like that.

178
00:12:53,877 --> 00:12:55,879
What? Then why'd you ask that?

179
00:12:55,963 --> 00:12:58,007
Forget it. Go to sleep.

180
00:13:00,676 --> 00:13:01,552
Good night.

181
00:14:38,148 --> 00:14:42,569
But if you've been friends for that long
and still haven't asked her out yet,

182
00:14:42,653 --> 00:14:44,530
doesn't that mean that's the extent
of your feelings for her?

183
00:14:48,951 --> 00:14:50,035
Asking her out…

184
00:15:18,147 --> 00:15:19,815
-Are you tired?
-Yeah, I am.

185
00:15:32,453 --> 00:15:33,454
This is just crazy.

186
00:15:34,038 --> 00:15:36,874
They both must've lost their minds.

187
00:15:36,957 --> 00:15:38,709
He was on a business trip with his wife.

188
00:15:42,171 --> 00:15:43,255
This is insane.

189
00:15:44,798 --> 00:15:46,383
Should I tell her or not?

190
00:15:47,342 --> 00:15:48,218
Come in.

191
00:15:53,348 --> 00:15:54,433
What is it?

192
00:15:54,516 --> 00:15:56,226
I brought the expense report
for the business trip.

193
00:15:57,311 --> 00:15:59,313
-You can leave it there.
-Okay.

194
00:16:01,774 --> 00:16:02,858
Wait, Ms. Go.

195
00:16:03,859 --> 00:16:04,860
Yes?

196
00:16:06,361 --> 00:16:08,781
Does it look like I have something to say?

197
00:16:10,115 --> 00:16:12,743
-Pardon?
-I mean, do I have

198
00:16:13,869 --> 00:16:15,079
something to tell you?

199
00:16:15,996 --> 00:16:18,123
What are you trying to say?

200
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:20,209
How about lunch together?

201
00:16:20,876 --> 00:16:22,711
Oh, that's what you're talking about.

202
00:16:23,212 --> 00:16:24,922
Did you know about it too?

203
00:16:25,005 --> 00:16:26,882
Then again, how could you not?

204
00:16:26,965 --> 00:16:28,550
News like that tends to spread quickly.

205
00:16:28,634 --> 00:16:30,052
You knew about it?

206
00:16:33,222 --> 00:16:34,139
Are you okay?

207
00:16:35,182 --> 00:16:36,391
I just heard about it.

208
00:16:38,227 --> 00:16:40,020
The cafeteria is serving samgyetang
for lunch today.

209
00:16:41,188 --> 00:16:43,482
Should we head on over together?

210
00:16:45,567 --> 00:16:46,777
What?

211
00:16:48,904 --> 00:16:52,282
My gosh, the chicken is so tender.
They cooked it so well.

212
00:16:53,742 --> 00:16:55,786
The soup is so rich.

213
00:16:56,453 --> 00:16:57,996
Do you not have any appetite, Jin-hui?

214
00:16:58,080 --> 00:17:00,582
Looking at this chicken

215
00:17:00,666 --> 00:17:03,877
reminds me of the samgyetang place
I went to a few days ago.

216
00:17:03,961 --> 00:17:06,004
You see, I went to this samgyetang place
a while ago, and…

217
00:17:10,926 --> 00:17:12,136
Come here.

218
00:17:12,719 --> 00:17:16,348
You see, I went to this samgyetang place
a few days ago,

219
00:17:16,431 --> 00:17:20,269
and I saw my best friend's husband

220
00:17:20,352 --> 00:17:26,150
pick the meat off the bone
to feed some ditzy young brat.

221
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:28,193
-So it's an affair.
-Yeah!

222
00:17:28,277 --> 00:17:31,196
They were all over each other,
kissing each other and stuff.

223
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:33,115
It was a total mess.

224
00:17:33,198 --> 00:17:35,659
Then what about your friend?

225
00:17:35,742 --> 00:17:38,495
Exactly. She's completely clueless.

226
00:17:38,579 --> 00:17:41,707
She was going on about how he started
wearing cologne and nice clothes,

227
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:44,042
and how it felt like
they were newlyweds again.

228
00:17:44,126 --> 00:17:46,044
-But they were all signs of cheating.
-Oh no.

229
00:17:46,128 --> 00:17:48,005
-Right.
-Totally.

230
00:17:48,797 --> 00:17:49,756
So?

231
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:51,592
Did you tell your friend?

232
00:17:52,176 --> 00:17:53,177
Sorry?

233
00:17:54,386 --> 00:17:56,305
No, not yet.

234
00:17:56,388 --> 00:17:58,932
It's been weighing on my mind.

235
00:17:59,016 --> 00:18:01,560
I don't know if I should tell her
or just keep it to myself.

236
00:18:01,643 --> 00:18:03,645
Right. It's a concern.

237
00:18:03,729 --> 00:18:06,523
-It's a legit concern.
-Right.

238
00:18:06,607 --> 00:18:07,608
Of course, you have to tell her.

239
00:18:07,691 --> 00:18:09,193
Do you want your friend
to stay in the dark?

240
00:18:09,276 --> 00:18:10,319
Right.

241
00:18:10,402 --> 00:18:13,947
From my experience,
that's not always the way to go.

242
00:18:14,031 --> 00:18:16,116
It could just be a fling.
A moment of weakness, if you will.

243
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,076
But if your friend finds out,

244
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:20,120
then there's no turning back.

245
00:18:20,871 --> 00:18:23,123
Yeah, it'll leave a scar on her forever.

246
00:18:23,207 --> 00:18:24,708
Just look the other way.

247
00:18:24,791 --> 00:18:26,668
-Maybe you're right.
-Yeah.

248
00:18:33,175 --> 00:18:36,220
KANGKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

249
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,186
Are you going somewhere?

250
00:18:45,854 --> 00:18:48,273
I want to go on a walk for some fresh air.

251
00:18:48,357 --> 00:18:49,608
Then let me accompany you.

252
00:18:50,692 --> 00:18:51,860
You don't need to worry.

253
00:18:52,694 --> 00:18:55,072
I won't leave the hospital building.

254
00:19:14,925 --> 00:19:17,678
Look at you go. Are you tired?

255
00:19:17,761 --> 00:19:19,429
Let's sit and take a break.

256
00:19:19,513 --> 00:19:20,639
Careful.

257
00:19:21,515 --> 00:19:22,557
There you go.

258
00:19:24,393 --> 00:19:25,852
You didn't need to come.

259
00:19:25,936 --> 00:19:28,772
How could I not?
I'd be worried sick if I didn't.

260
00:19:28,855 --> 00:19:31,608
I'll gladly follow you
to the ends of the earth.

261
00:19:34,861 --> 00:19:35,946
-Thank you.
-Of course.

262
00:19:36,029 --> 00:19:38,991
Once you get better,
let's go travel abroad.

263
00:19:39,074 --> 00:19:40,784
Oh no. What are they going to do?

264
00:19:40,867 --> 00:19:43,245
-They're going to get caught.
-Oh no.

265
00:19:43,787 --> 00:19:45,163
They're going to fall.

266
00:19:45,247 --> 00:19:46,498
-Oh gosh.
-What are they going to do?

267
00:19:47,499 --> 00:19:49,418
They get me every time.

268
00:19:49,501 --> 00:19:51,295
Have some while you watch.

269
00:19:51,378 --> 00:19:52,921
-It's good.
-My daughter brought them.

270
00:19:53,005 --> 00:19:55,007
I wish I had a daughter too.

271
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:56,800
-Have some.
-It's good.

272
00:20:00,387 --> 00:20:01,763
They'll get into big trouble if they fall.

273
00:20:01,847 --> 00:20:03,181
Would you like one?

274
00:20:06,476 --> 00:20:08,979
No, thank you. I'm okay.

275
00:20:10,564 --> 00:20:11,857
SANDWICH BISCUIT

276
00:20:11,940 --> 00:20:14,526
I didn't eat any of it.

277
00:20:14,609 --> 00:20:18,905
My daughter ripped the packaging for me
because I was too weak after surgery.

278
00:20:20,198 --> 00:20:22,117
Try it. It's soft and delicious.

279
00:20:23,118 --> 00:20:25,662
-I said I'm okay.
-It's fine, take it.

280
00:20:25,746 --> 00:20:27,247
-No, really. I'm fine.
-Just eat…

281
00:20:33,211 --> 00:20:34,212
I'm sorry.

282
00:20:35,047 --> 00:20:37,841
I was being too forceful.

283
00:20:39,885 --> 00:20:41,219
It's fine.

284
00:20:42,971 --> 00:20:44,473
Everyone

285
00:20:45,057 --> 00:20:47,559
has their ups and downs in life.

286
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:51,229
After my husband passed,

287
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:55,150
there were many times
when I just wanted to end my life.

288
00:20:55,233 --> 00:20:58,653
But I couldn't go through with it
when I thought about my kids.

289
00:20:59,654 --> 00:21:01,073
As a mom,

290
00:21:01,823 --> 00:21:04,868
how could I hurt my kids like that?

291
00:21:04,951 --> 00:21:09,122
When I forced myself to keep going,
I found myself getting by somehow.

292
00:21:10,457 --> 00:21:12,084
What's your story…

293
00:21:13,543 --> 00:21:14,378
Oh gosh.

294
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:18,965
I'm sorry,
I think I may have spoken out of line.

295
00:21:21,426 --> 00:21:22,260
Yes.

296
00:21:22,344 --> 00:21:24,096
You really did.

297
00:21:25,138 --> 00:21:28,100
I never said I wanted to hear your story.

298
00:21:29,684 --> 00:21:31,019
Oh dear.

299
00:21:32,104 --> 00:21:33,063
I just meant…

300
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:36,942
What's wrong with me?

301
00:21:55,127 --> 00:21:56,586
I'm home.

302
00:21:56,670 --> 00:21:58,213
Oh, hey. You're here.

303
00:21:58,713 --> 00:21:59,589
What are you up to?

304
00:21:59,673 --> 00:22:02,676
I'm just choosing photos
for the ad concept.

305
00:22:02,759 --> 00:22:05,178
-How are they?
-Not bad. Take a look.

306
00:22:05,262 --> 00:22:06,096
Okay.

307
00:22:06,930 --> 00:22:08,557
They look nice.

308
00:22:08,640 --> 00:22:09,724
-You think so?
-Yeah.

309
00:22:11,393 --> 00:22:12,436
What's that?

310
00:22:13,061 --> 00:22:14,438
Oh, this?

311
00:22:14,521 --> 00:22:16,523
It's our reformulated baby lotion.

312
00:22:16,606 --> 00:22:18,525
Can you test it
and tell me what you think?

313
00:22:18,608 --> 00:22:20,402
It was a favor
from the product development team.

314
00:22:20,485 --> 00:22:22,654
If Jun's sleeping right now,
try it tomorrow morning.

315
00:22:22,737 --> 00:22:23,655
Let me try it now.

316
00:22:24,489 --> 00:22:27,409
I share Jun's lotion,
so I'll be able to tell.

317
00:22:30,078 --> 00:22:33,039
It goes on smoothly and feels hydrating.

318
00:22:33,623 --> 00:22:35,375
Hold on. Let me see the ingredients.

319
00:22:36,126 --> 00:22:37,961
It's the best one
out of all the ones I've used recently.

320
00:22:38,044 --> 00:22:40,005
Really? Okay.

321
00:22:40,088 --> 00:22:42,632
But why do you use Jun's lotion?
Don't you have your own?

322
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:45,719
That's just what happens
when you're raising a kid.

323
00:22:45,802 --> 00:22:48,471
You use whatever is left on your hand
after applying it on them.

324
00:22:48,555 --> 00:22:50,932
You have to hug them,
hold them, and play with them.

325
00:22:51,016 --> 00:22:53,518
If I use the wrong adult lotion,
it could irritate their skin.

326
00:22:53,602 --> 00:22:54,686
I see.

327
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:57,105
Then what about the scent?

328
00:22:57,689 --> 00:22:58,982
Is it okay for adults to use?

329
00:22:59,065 --> 00:22:59,983
The scent?

330
00:23:01,943 --> 00:23:04,112
It just smells like baby powder.

331
00:23:27,594 --> 00:23:29,471
The powdery note is strong.

332
00:23:30,222 --> 00:23:34,017
But as you said, if parents use
the same lotion as their kids,

333
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:36,144
a scent that's too baby-like
might not be the best, no?

334
00:23:37,187 --> 00:23:38,647
-What?
-Right?

335
00:23:39,981 --> 00:23:41,608
Oh, right.

336
00:23:41,691 --> 00:23:43,985
Imagine if they were
regular office workers.

337
00:23:44,861 --> 00:23:45,946
Yeah, you're right.

338
00:23:46,029 --> 00:23:47,572
I guess it could feel a bit out of place

339
00:23:47,656 --> 00:23:49,741
to smell like baby powder
at a business meeting.

340
00:23:49,824 --> 00:23:50,700
Yeah.

341
00:23:50,784 --> 00:23:54,162
For now, I should suggest
they make this unscented.

342
00:23:54,246 --> 00:23:55,455
That was really helpful.

343
00:23:55,538 --> 00:23:57,582
Thanks, friend. I'm off.

344
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:00,043
Okay, sure.

345
00:24:00,126 --> 00:24:01,920
-Bye.
-Bye. Thank you.

346
00:24:07,092 --> 00:24:07,926
Kim Seon-u?

347
00:24:09,469 --> 00:24:10,553
That no-name photographer?

348
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:13,390
I already told you he's a no!

349
00:24:13,473 --> 00:24:15,517
Come on, have some standards.

350
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,726
Why did you even appoint someone

351
00:24:16,810 --> 00:24:19,688
who couldn't secure a diploma in the US

352
00:24:19,771 --> 00:24:21,356
as the deputy director in the first place?

353
00:24:21,439 --> 00:24:22,649
You take care of this.

354
00:24:23,233 --> 00:24:25,986
I wonder if David Kim
is done with his exhibition in New York.

355
00:24:27,821 --> 00:24:30,282
Ji-hyeok chose him, not me.

356
00:24:30,991 --> 00:24:33,285
What? Ji-hyeok did?

357
00:24:35,870 --> 00:24:38,707
-Then just proceed as is for now.
-Honey!

358
00:24:38,790 --> 00:24:40,125
I'll put my trust in Gong Ji-hyeok.

359
00:24:40,208 --> 00:24:43,962
Even Tae-yeong acknowledged that Ji-hyeok
had an undeniably discerning eye.

360
00:24:44,045 --> 00:24:47,173
Whenever he found a promising startup
worth investing in,

361
00:24:47,257 --> 00:24:50,552
Ji-hyeok had more often than not
already signed them.

362
00:24:51,511 --> 00:24:54,472
It means he has good instincts
and works fast.

363
00:24:54,556 --> 00:24:56,933
If our Tae-yeong approves of him,

364
00:24:57,017 --> 00:24:58,059
then I suppose I'll trust him.

365
00:24:58,143 --> 00:24:59,936
When he returns next week,

366
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:02,564
we should have a meal
with Chairman Gong's family.

367
00:25:03,148 --> 00:25:04,065
We should.

368
00:25:06,359 --> 00:25:09,529
Mr. Kang, can you confirm you received
the pictures I sent for the ad concept?

369
00:25:10,071 --> 00:25:10,947
Yes.

370
00:25:11,031 --> 00:25:12,490
Okay, I'll see you at the office later.

371
00:25:31,134 --> 00:25:33,636
If parents use the same lotion
as their kids,

372
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:35,930
a scent that's too baby-like
might not be the best, no?

373
00:26:03,375 --> 00:26:04,876
Mr. Kim!

374
00:26:08,713 --> 00:26:09,547
Hello.

375
00:26:10,799 --> 00:26:14,094
Why are you all dressed up?
You're making my heart flutter.

376
00:26:16,596 --> 00:26:17,806
You smell good too.

377
00:26:18,390 --> 00:26:19,891
My makeup also looks good today.

378
00:26:20,683 --> 00:26:21,601
And I'm wearing a cute outfit.

379
00:26:24,187 --> 00:26:26,606
Should we take some first birthday photos
after the meeting?

380
00:26:26,689 --> 00:26:28,108
Might as well take some
since I look pretty.

381
00:26:28,191 --> 00:26:29,567
Well…

382
00:26:30,568 --> 00:26:33,822
-Today might be a bit--
-Forget it then.

383
00:26:33,905 --> 00:26:35,990
I'll just spill the beans.

384
00:26:40,703 --> 00:26:41,663
All right.

385
00:26:42,831 --> 00:26:43,665
Let's do it.

386
00:26:44,249 --> 00:26:45,166
Let's take some.

387
00:26:45,250 --> 00:26:46,084
Okay!

388
00:26:53,383 --> 00:26:54,300
Mr. Gong.

389
00:26:55,093 --> 00:26:55,969
Did you two…

390
00:26:57,470 --> 00:26:58,304
come together?

391
00:26:59,013 --> 00:27:01,182
No, we met on the first floor.

392
00:27:01,975 --> 00:27:02,851
See you later.

393
00:27:02,934 --> 00:27:04,060
We should head inside.

394
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:15,405
She was going on about how he started
wearing cologne and nice clothes,

395
00:27:15,488 --> 00:27:17,824
and how it felt like
they were newlyweds again.

396
00:27:17,907 --> 00:27:20,076
-But they were all signs of cheating.
-Oh no.

397
00:27:32,714 --> 00:27:33,631
You sure about this?

398
00:27:34,299 --> 00:27:35,884
Your wife works here.

399
00:27:37,719 --> 00:27:39,637
That's what makes it more fun.

400
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:42,098
It makes it thrilling.

401
00:27:44,726 --> 00:27:45,560
Naughty boy.

402
00:28:14,297 --> 00:28:15,340
What's wrong with you?

403
00:28:16,257 --> 00:28:17,467
This is where I always sit.

404
00:28:18,384 --> 00:28:19,552
Find another seat.

405
00:28:29,229 --> 00:28:31,147
-Thank you.
-Here's the proposal.

406
00:28:32,106 --> 00:28:33,274
-Hold on.
-What?

407
00:28:35,944 --> 00:28:36,945
Look.

408
00:28:37,654 --> 00:28:39,405
Oh my. Nan-suk, look.

409
00:28:39,489 --> 00:28:43,827
-He's so sweet.
-They're always so lovey-dovey.

410
00:28:43,910 --> 00:28:46,412
-Thank you.
-He's just naturally sweet.

411
00:28:47,831 --> 00:28:49,332
Goodness gracious.

412
00:28:51,709 --> 00:28:53,628
-Trash.
-Mr. Gong.

413
00:28:55,046 --> 00:28:55,922
Mr. Gong?

414
00:28:56,422 --> 00:28:57,465
What?

415
00:28:58,049 --> 00:29:00,885
Could you tell us which concept
you prefer between the final two?

416
00:29:00,969 --> 00:29:02,512
Well, let's see.

417
00:29:04,138 --> 00:29:05,431
Let's ask the others first.

418
00:29:06,850 --> 00:29:08,351
Personally,

419
00:29:08,434 --> 00:29:10,395
I think the one on the right
would be better.

420
00:29:10,478 --> 00:29:13,189
If we want our consumers
to emotionally connect

421
00:29:13,273 --> 00:29:15,066
with the feeling of parental care,

422
00:29:15,149 --> 00:29:18,862
I think it'd be better for the focus
to be on people rather than trees.

423
00:29:18,945 --> 00:29:23,074
But wouldn't that obscure the message
behind our environmental campaign launch?

424
00:29:23,157 --> 00:29:27,287
You have a point. To make sure it doesn't,
we should show more of the trees.

425
00:29:27,370 --> 00:29:29,497
If we do go with option two,

426
00:29:29,581 --> 00:29:32,667
I think it'd be nice to have
a more front-facing shot of the kids.

427
00:29:32,750 --> 00:29:33,626
Why these two…

428
00:29:33,710 --> 00:29:35,670
Hey, have you seriously lost your mind?

429
00:29:35,753 --> 00:29:38,840
-Yes.
-Maybe we should just make both posters.

430
00:29:40,174 --> 00:29:42,510
One focusing on trees,
and another on people.

431
00:29:42,594 --> 00:29:43,595
Okay.

432
00:29:43,678 --> 00:29:45,722
And the copy can also be different.

433
00:29:45,805 --> 00:29:47,724
You think so?
We don't need to make them the same?

434
00:29:47,807 --> 00:29:50,685
The format can be similar,
but I think the content can be different.

435
00:29:51,436 --> 00:29:52,520
I think that'd be good.

436
00:29:53,438 --> 00:29:54,439
And…

437
00:29:56,107 --> 00:29:57,233
Thank you.

438
00:29:57,317 --> 00:29:59,444
The poster with the focus on people
can be worked on by Ms. Jang and--

439
00:29:59,527 --> 00:30:00,528
-I'd like to do it.
-Okay.

440
00:30:00,612 --> 00:30:01,946
-Jin-hui.
-Yeah!

441
00:30:02,530 --> 00:30:06,993
Then Ms. Bae and Ms. Lee can work on
the one that focuses on the trees.

442
00:30:07,076 --> 00:30:09,287
That concludes our meeting.
Let's go have lunch.

443
00:30:09,370 --> 00:30:12,290
Mr. Kim and Ms. Yu, why don't you join us?

444
00:30:13,374 --> 00:30:16,127
-Should I?
-Yeah, you should.

445
00:30:16,210 --> 00:30:17,378
I'm skipping because of my gastritis.

446
00:30:18,087 --> 00:30:19,881
-Are you still feeling sick?
-Yeah.

447
00:30:20,590 --> 00:30:22,175
Then why don't we go out
and have some porridge?

448
00:30:27,931 --> 00:30:30,975
Oh, right. I forgot I had something to do.

449
00:30:31,059 --> 00:30:32,018
Sorry.

450
00:30:32,101 --> 00:30:34,020
It's fine. Work is more important.

451
00:30:34,103 --> 00:30:34,938
Don't worry about me.

452
00:30:35,521 --> 00:30:36,356
Are they being serious?

453
00:30:36,439 --> 00:30:39,150
-Let's head out together, Mr. Kim.
-Sure.

454
00:30:39,233 --> 00:30:41,527
Ms. Yu, why don't you join me for lunch?

455
00:30:42,111 --> 00:30:43,780
I have something to discuss with you
regarding work.

456
00:30:43,863 --> 00:30:45,406
I'm sorry,
but I also have a prior engagement.

457
00:30:45,990 --> 00:30:47,158
-Let's go, Mr. Kim.
-I'm off.

458
00:30:47,241 --> 00:30:48,076
Okay, bye.

459
00:30:48,159 --> 00:30:49,410
Bye, Ms. Yu.

460
00:31:10,223 --> 00:31:12,642
Food that's good for the stomach.

461
00:31:14,602 --> 00:31:16,729
"Porridge or ginger tea."

462
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:21,567
LOVE PORRIDGE

463
00:31:22,402 --> 00:31:23,695
What's this?

464
00:31:26,114 --> 00:31:26,948
Abalone porridge.

465
00:31:27,031 --> 00:31:29,158
I ordered beef porridge,
but they got my order wrong.

466
00:31:29,909 --> 00:31:31,411
I'm allergic to abalones,

467
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:34,747
but I couldn't waste perfectly good food.

468
00:31:34,831 --> 00:31:35,665
Oh, I see.

469
00:31:35,748 --> 00:31:37,834
Then why don't you ask them
to make a new one?

470
00:31:37,917 --> 00:31:39,961
It's fine. You eat it.

471
00:31:51,889 --> 00:31:53,725
How about we make it round?

472
00:31:53,808 --> 00:31:54,976
I'll leave a note.

473
00:31:55,059 --> 00:31:56,144
-Great.
-It could be bigger.

474
00:31:56,227 --> 00:31:57,687
-Have a drink, everyone.
-Yeah, I agree.

475
00:31:57,770 --> 00:31:59,731
-Oh, coffee.
-Coffee!

476
00:31:59,814 --> 00:32:01,941
Coffee after lunch!

477
00:32:02,025 --> 00:32:03,026
Ginger tea?

478
00:32:04,068 --> 00:32:05,361
Why'd you get ginger tea?

479
00:32:05,862 --> 00:32:07,655
They were half price
at the shop out front.

480
00:32:08,531 --> 00:32:09,490
Just the ginger tea.

481
00:32:51,199 --> 00:32:53,576
I saw you earlier today.
What brings you here?

482
00:32:54,786 --> 00:32:56,454
You seem to be in a great mood.

483
00:32:57,288 --> 00:33:00,083
Where did you go after the meeting?

484
00:33:02,752 --> 00:33:03,586
Ji-hyeok,

485
00:33:04,212 --> 00:33:05,671
I have a crush on someone.

486
00:33:06,339 --> 00:33:09,175
I haven't had a chance
to tell my parents yet,

487
00:33:09,842 --> 00:33:11,427
-but our marriage--
-No.

488
00:33:11,511 --> 00:33:12,595
You can't.

489
00:33:13,179 --> 00:33:14,305
What?

490
00:33:15,264 --> 00:33:16,390
He's a married…

491
00:33:17,767 --> 00:33:18,976
He's a married man.

492
00:33:19,060 --> 00:33:20,770
He has a wife and a kid.

493
00:33:21,354 --> 00:33:22,188
What?

494
00:33:22,814 --> 00:33:23,898
I saw you and Kim Seon-u…

495
00:33:25,566 --> 00:33:26,484
kissing.

496
00:33:27,693 --> 00:33:30,196
I passed off your selfish
and immature behavior up until now

497
00:33:30,279 --> 00:33:31,739
as being cute.

498
00:33:31,823 --> 00:33:33,157
But this is just wrong.

499
00:33:33,241 --> 00:33:35,118
You've crossed way over the line.

500
00:33:35,201 --> 00:33:36,911
Are you saying you want to go through
with this marriage?

501
00:33:36,994 --> 00:33:39,705
You're the one who said
there would be no love between us.

502
00:33:39,789 --> 00:33:40,706
So?

503
00:33:41,457 --> 00:33:43,835
Is this your way of protesting?
To prevent this marriage?

504
00:33:43,918 --> 00:33:45,294
Stop playing with fire.

505
00:33:46,045 --> 00:33:47,505
And stop trying to use people.

506
00:33:47,588 --> 00:33:49,090
I'm not playing with fire.

507
00:33:49,173 --> 00:33:50,758
And I'm definitely not using him.

508
00:33:51,342 --> 00:33:53,344
Then what is it?

509
00:33:53,427 --> 00:33:54,804
The truth is, he's…

510
00:33:54,887 --> 00:33:55,805
Could you

511
00:33:55,888 --> 00:33:58,850
keep this a secret?

512
00:33:58,933 --> 00:33:59,976
Please.

513
00:34:03,688 --> 00:34:05,523
I'm going through with this marriage,
no matter what.

514
00:34:06,107 --> 00:34:07,400
And once we're married,

515
00:34:07,483 --> 00:34:08,985
I won't tolerate infidelity.

516
00:34:09,861 --> 00:34:11,737
You should show respect
even if it's a loveless marriage.

517
00:34:12,321 --> 00:34:13,197
I mean, why?

518
00:34:13,281 --> 00:34:15,741
Why do you want to get married
all of a sudden?

519
00:34:16,617 --> 00:34:17,910
You only care about your own feelings,
don't you?

520
00:34:18,494 --> 00:34:20,746
Don't you realize
you're destroying a family?

521
00:34:22,081 --> 00:34:22,999
Ms. Go

522
00:34:24,167 --> 00:34:26,377
is just an ordinary woman and mother.

523
00:34:26,460 --> 00:34:27,378
If she finds out…

524
00:34:31,799 --> 00:34:32,758
her world will crumble.

525
00:34:32,842 --> 00:34:36,053
No, it won't. This is driving me crazy.

526
00:34:38,848 --> 00:34:41,976
Why are you even worried about her?

527
00:34:46,147 --> 00:34:47,356
Because she's my team member.

528
00:34:48,691 --> 00:34:50,234
I trust you understood.

529
00:34:51,235 --> 00:34:52,236
I'm off.

530
00:35:14,800 --> 00:35:15,801
What's this?

531
00:35:16,344 --> 00:35:17,178
Abalone porridge.

532
00:35:17,261 --> 00:35:18,554
-Have a drink, everyone.
-Yeah, I agree.

533
00:35:18,638 --> 00:35:20,014
-Oh, coffee.
-Coffee!

534
00:35:20,097 --> 00:35:21,182
Ginger tea?

535
00:35:22,141 --> 00:35:23,517
They were half price
at the shop out front.

536
00:35:24,352 --> 00:35:25,311
Just the ginger tea.

537
00:36:07,478 --> 00:36:08,312
Come in.

538
00:36:15,069 --> 00:36:15,903
There's something

539
00:36:16,862 --> 00:36:19,573
I want to give you
before the presentation.

540
00:36:23,286 --> 00:36:24,120
Here.

541
00:36:30,835 --> 00:36:31,836
This is…

542
00:36:31,919 --> 00:36:34,046
It's the clover from last time.

543
00:36:40,845 --> 00:36:43,055
You picked it up and kept it?

544
00:36:43,139 --> 00:36:45,182
It would've been a waste.
I worked hard to find it.

545
00:36:46,183 --> 00:36:48,269
Turns out, this is pretty effective.

546
00:36:48,352 --> 00:36:50,146
It brought this wonderful person
into my life

547
00:36:51,063 --> 00:36:53,024
who paid off my debt,

548
00:36:53,107 --> 00:36:55,735
bought me porridge, and more.

549
00:36:57,320 --> 00:37:00,531
I'm sure it'll bring you good luck
for your presentation as well.

550
00:37:00,614 --> 00:37:02,491
So take it with you and see what it does.

551
00:37:04,076 --> 00:37:05,703
I have to say I do feel a bit guilty

552
00:37:06,620 --> 00:37:07,955
for receiving so much support.

553
00:37:09,457 --> 00:37:10,833
I pursued this campaign

554
00:37:12,501 --> 00:37:14,295
with a bit of a personal motive.

555
00:37:17,798 --> 00:37:21,844
You want to carry on
your mother's work, right?

556
00:37:23,346 --> 00:37:25,056
"I want to protect my child."

557
00:37:25,973 --> 00:37:28,434
"I want him to live in a better world."

558
00:37:30,144 --> 00:37:34,607
I hope your mother's sentiment
is received well.

559
00:37:36,108 --> 00:37:38,652
Because that's a sentiment
shared by all parents.

560
00:37:46,118 --> 00:37:49,121
I just rambled on and on, didn't I?

561
00:37:49,205 --> 00:37:51,957
I'll leave you to get ready.

562
00:37:54,585 --> 00:37:55,628
You got this.

563
00:38:11,268 --> 00:38:13,062
Hey, TF!

564
00:38:13,145 --> 00:38:15,022
Wait, where are your shovels?

565
00:38:15,106 --> 00:38:17,483
You should've brought them with you.

566
00:38:18,150 --> 00:38:20,111
I heard you were just shoveling nonsense
to prepare for this campaign.

567
00:38:21,070 --> 00:38:22,405
Anyhow,

568
00:38:22,988 --> 00:38:25,241
I look forward to your brilliant nonsense.

569
00:38:29,829 --> 00:38:32,790
Do we actually have a shovel?
I'd love to bury him alive.

570
00:38:33,666 --> 00:38:36,544
He just needs to wait and see
who laughs in the end.

571
00:38:37,336 --> 00:38:38,963
Okay, let's go win this thing.

572
00:38:46,137 --> 00:38:47,638
"Ten Pocket Kids."

573
00:38:47,721 --> 00:38:49,265
It means for one child,

574
00:38:49,348 --> 00:38:51,308
as many as ten wallets open,
from parents and relatives

575
00:38:51,392 --> 00:38:53,018
to even family friends.

576
00:38:53,644 --> 00:38:56,105
In other words, fewer kids
mean a more privileged upbringing.

577
00:38:56,689 --> 00:38:58,524
We incorporated this sentiment

578
00:38:58,607 --> 00:39:01,485
into our marketing strategy
to elevate Natural BeBe

579
00:39:01,569 --> 00:39:03,279
into a global luxury brand.

580
00:39:03,362 --> 00:39:06,240
This is the "Born to Be Luxury" campaign.

581
00:39:07,032 --> 00:39:10,786
As you're aware, this is Jessica,
a Hollywood star and a global influencer

582
00:39:11,412 --> 00:39:13,497
with over 300 million followers worldwide.

583
00:39:13,581 --> 00:39:14,874
We proposed the idea

584
00:39:14,957 --> 00:39:17,418
of showcasing her parenting moments
on social media while using our products,

585
00:39:18,210 --> 00:39:20,004
and we've made significant headway.

586
00:39:20,087 --> 00:39:21,589
How far along are you?

587
00:39:21,672 --> 00:39:23,632
We can sign the contract
and bring her on board

588
00:39:23,716 --> 00:39:25,551
the second you approve the campaign.

589
00:39:34,935 --> 00:39:37,188
MOTHER TF

590
00:39:39,148 --> 00:39:40,065
Luxury?

591
00:39:40,149 --> 00:39:41,025
It's nice.

592
00:39:42,234 --> 00:39:45,029
But is Natural BeBe
a company that sells luxury goods?

593
00:39:46,322 --> 00:39:47,615
No.

594
00:39:47,698 --> 00:39:48,866
Natural BeBe…

595
00:39:51,035 --> 00:39:53,370
is a company
that makes essential products.

596
00:39:54,497 --> 00:39:57,208
Products accessible
to anyone raising children.

597
00:39:57,917 --> 00:39:58,918
The essentials.

598
00:40:00,044 --> 00:40:03,547
Director Choi, how did it feel
when you first held your child?

599
00:40:03,631 --> 00:40:06,383
Did you wish for them
to make more money than others?

600
00:40:06,467 --> 00:40:09,678
Or did you wish for them
to become a prodigy,

601
00:40:09,762 --> 00:40:11,222
skilled in sports or studies?

602
00:40:11,305 --> 00:40:13,265
No parent would wish for such things.

603
00:40:13,849 --> 00:40:16,894
You just wish for your child
to grow up healthy.

604
00:40:17,561 --> 00:40:18,729
Don't you agree, sir?

605
00:40:19,313 --> 00:40:20,272
Yeah.

606
00:40:20,356 --> 00:40:21,273
That's right.

607
00:40:21,357 --> 00:40:24,818
For the simple wish
that their child grows up safe and sound,

608
00:40:25,402 --> 00:40:28,239
parents bear the heaviest burden
in the world,

609
00:40:28,822 --> 00:40:30,616
and they do so willingly.

610
00:40:31,408 --> 00:40:33,619
Natural BeBe shouldn't encourage parents

611
00:40:33,702 --> 00:40:36,539
to compare their children
and raise them to outshine others.

612
00:40:36,622 --> 00:40:38,791
Shouldn't we become their partners

613
00:40:40,167 --> 00:40:42,336
who will share that heavy burden instead?

614
00:40:43,337 --> 00:40:45,839
Inspired by a desire
to stand by every parent out there,

615
00:40:46,799 --> 00:40:47,675
we make this proposal.

616
00:40:48,467 --> 00:40:49,301
This is

617
00:40:50,427 --> 00:40:52,513
the tree-planting CSR campaign,

618
00:40:52,596 --> 00:40:55,516
"A Green Future We Draw Together."

619
00:40:56,517 --> 00:40:59,436
How exactly does tree-planting fit in?

620
00:41:01,397 --> 00:41:03,691
On the left, you'll see the sapling

621
00:41:03,774 --> 00:41:06,902
that was planted 20 years ago
as part of Natural BeBe's CSR initiative.

622
00:41:06,986 --> 00:41:10,281
And on the right,
you'll see it in its current state.

623
00:41:10,948 --> 00:41:12,157
While I grew up,

624
00:41:12,241 --> 00:41:17,913
so did this tree to provide fresh,
clean air to this day.

625
00:41:18,497 --> 00:41:21,417
And it'll continue to do so
as I bring a child into this world

626
00:41:21,500 --> 00:41:22,835
to grow up alongside it.

627
00:41:24,253 --> 00:41:25,629
Planting a tree

628
00:41:26,505 --> 00:41:29,133
means fostering healthy growth.

629
00:41:30,092 --> 00:41:31,385
And isn't that…

630
00:41:33,137 --> 00:41:34,972
what we do best?

631
00:41:47,526 --> 00:41:51,322
"In ten years, who will be taller?
You or the tree?"

632
00:41:52,072 --> 00:41:54,283
"It won't matter who wins,

633
00:41:54,366 --> 00:41:56,952
as long as you grow up
strong and healthy."

634
00:42:00,789 --> 00:42:02,166
"Big or small,

635
00:42:02,249 --> 00:42:03,792
yellow or red,

636
00:42:03,876 --> 00:42:05,336
I like trees for being trees,

637
00:42:05,419 --> 00:42:06,295
and I like you

638
00:42:06,879 --> 00:42:08,088
for being you."

639
00:42:09,715 --> 00:42:11,425
"It's important to be someone
without a dark shadow,

640
00:42:12,176 --> 00:42:14,053
but I hope you grow up to be
someone who knows

641
00:42:14,136 --> 00:42:15,512
how precious a shade can be."

642
00:42:20,768 --> 00:42:23,103
"Watching you search
for a four-leaf clover

643
00:42:24,688 --> 00:42:28,776
is already my greatest fortune."

644
00:42:47,336 --> 00:42:50,631
In hopes of a healthy world where all kids
can run and play without worry,

645
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:55,719
Natural BeBe continues to foster a forest
that will grow with the kids.

646
00:42:55,803 --> 00:42:57,388
This is "A Green Future We Draw Together"

647
00:42:57,471 --> 00:42:58,597
by Natural Bebe.

648
00:43:27,126 --> 00:43:28,043
Good work.

649
00:43:34,425 --> 00:43:35,426
You too.

650
00:43:51,024 --> 00:43:51,859
What are you doing?

651
00:43:55,946 --> 00:43:57,448
Mr. Gong!

652
00:43:59,700 --> 00:44:01,618
-We did it!
-We did it!

653
00:44:08,667 --> 00:44:10,627
Good job, everyone!

654
00:44:11,128 --> 00:44:13,088
-Good job, everyone!
-Good job, everyone!

655
00:44:13,797 --> 00:44:15,007
Good job.

656
00:44:17,092 --> 00:44:18,385
You said you had gastritis.

657
00:44:18,886 --> 00:44:21,138
I need to have a drink on a day like this.

658
00:44:21,680 --> 00:44:23,557
I coated my stomach with medicine earlier.

659
00:44:23,640 --> 00:44:25,392
Then you should
at least eat something first.

660
00:44:31,732 --> 00:44:32,733
Okay.

661
00:44:33,525 --> 00:44:35,527
Mr. Gong.

662
00:44:35,611 --> 00:44:38,864
I totally fell for you today.

663
00:44:38,947 --> 00:44:40,657
You're such an excellent presenter.

664
00:44:40,741 --> 00:44:42,534
You were so eloquent.

665
00:44:42,618 --> 00:44:46,205
You know, if he tried to sell me
electric jade mats,

666
00:44:46,288 --> 00:44:47,748
I would have one in every room
in my house.

667
00:44:47,831 --> 00:44:48,665
Me too.

668
00:44:48,749 --> 00:44:50,417
-I'd buy them all.
-I agree. You were amazing.

669
00:44:50,501 --> 00:44:54,713
That's why I've stayed by his side
for all these years.

670
00:44:55,214 --> 00:44:56,715
It's all thanks to your hard work.

671
00:44:57,299 --> 00:44:59,218
You should feel proud
of the fact that you beat

672
00:44:59,801 --> 00:45:01,887
our company's marketing team
with your skills alone.

673
00:45:01,970 --> 00:45:02,930
Let's clink our glasses.

674
00:45:03,931 --> 00:45:06,183
-I'm about to tear up.
-Me too.

675
00:45:06,266 --> 00:45:08,477
Come on now, everyone.

676
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:10,103
Okay, what should we order next?

677
00:45:10,187 --> 00:45:12,147
Lobster? Pasta?

678
00:45:12,231 --> 00:45:13,899
Order anything and as much as you'd like.

679
00:45:13,982 --> 00:45:15,901
It'll be Mr. Gong's treat tonight.

680
00:45:15,984 --> 00:45:17,486
-Oh my, really?
-For real?

681
00:45:17,569 --> 00:45:19,154
Can I order enough for my breakfast?

682
00:45:21,281 --> 00:45:24,409
Excuse me,
what's the most expensive dish here?

683
00:45:24,493 --> 00:45:25,369
I'm curious too.

684
00:45:27,663 --> 00:45:29,540
-Amazing. They sell abalones here.
-Oh my.

685
00:45:29,623 --> 00:45:31,041
-Abalones?
-We have to order this.

686
00:45:31,124 --> 00:45:32,543
-One per table.
-Good call.

687
00:45:32,626 --> 00:45:33,460
That sounds so good.

688
00:45:41,969 --> 00:45:42,886
Hold on.

689
00:45:42,970 --> 00:45:46,682
We should've invited Mr. Kim and Ms. Yu.

690
00:45:46,765 --> 00:45:48,183
We all worked on it together.

691
00:45:48,267 --> 00:45:49,309
They're both busy.

692
00:45:49,393 --> 00:45:51,270
They said they'd drop by
if they finish early.

693
00:45:51,353 --> 00:45:52,604
I wonder if they'll make it.

694
00:45:54,064 --> 00:45:55,857
We should wait all night if we have to.

695
00:45:55,941 --> 00:45:56,817
We must.

696
00:46:00,696 --> 00:46:02,239
Mr. Kim! Over here.

697
00:46:04,241 --> 00:46:05,617
-Come over here.
-Sorry?

698
00:46:05,701 --> 00:46:06,743
Oh gosh.

699
00:46:09,329 --> 00:46:10,163
Ta-da!

700
00:46:10,247 --> 00:46:12,040
What's all this?

701
00:46:12,124 --> 00:46:14,251
-It's a party table for my first birthday.
-What?

702
00:46:18,755 --> 00:46:19,923
I'm ready.

703
00:46:21,049 --> 00:46:22,050
Here we go.

704
00:46:23,594 --> 00:46:24,845
Can you smile a little?

705
00:46:24,928 --> 00:46:25,971
Great.

706
00:46:26,054 --> 00:46:27,431
Can you take a bite of the food?

707
00:46:28,098 --> 00:46:30,350
Great. That looks good.

708
00:46:32,728 --> 00:46:35,105
Pardon me for a second.

709
00:46:57,419 --> 00:47:00,797
JI-HYEOK

710
00:47:00,881 --> 00:47:02,257
YU HA-YEONG

711
00:47:02,341 --> 00:47:04,301
-Why aren't you drinking?
-Isn't it so good?

712
00:47:07,888 --> 00:47:09,890
What? Who finished this?

713
00:47:11,183 --> 00:47:12,559
This is amazing.

714
00:47:14,519 --> 00:47:16,647
Who drinks wine like it's water?

715
00:47:16,730 --> 00:47:17,856
You see,

716
00:47:17,939 --> 00:47:20,275
I'm in such a good mood.

717
00:47:20,359 --> 00:47:22,194
I'm so happy right now.

718
00:47:23,070 --> 00:47:25,989
-Here's the abalone risotto and lasagna.
-Oh my!

719
00:47:26,073 --> 00:47:28,533
-That looks so good.
-Oh my goodness!

720
00:47:28,617 --> 00:47:30,160
-Thank you.
-I can't believe it.

721
00:47:30,243 --> 00:47:31,244
Mr. Gong.

722
00:47:31,328 --> 00:47:34,498
Please have the first bite!

723
00:47:35,040 --> 00:47:36,249
Why, thank you.

724
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:38,043
-Give me some too.
-Okay.

725
00:47:44,841 --> 00:47:46,301
Their abalone is really good.

726
00:47:48,261 --> 00:47:50,055
I'm allergic to abalones,

727
00:47:50,764 --> 00:47:52,391
but I couldn't waste perfectly good food.

728
00:47:56,687 --> 00:47:57,688
Oh, right.

729
00:47:57,771 --> 00:47:59,439
Jin-hui, what's the update on your friend?

730
00:47:59,523 --> 00:48:02,609
Did you tell her
about her husband cheating?

731
00:48:02,693 --> 00:48:04,111
I didn't even get a chance to.

732
00:48:04,194 --> 00:48:05,362
That bastard…

733
00:48:06,655 --> 00:48:08,490
I mean, her husband confessed.

734
00:48:08,573 --> 00:48:09,908
-Oh my.
-What?

735
00:48:09,991 --> 00:48:11,118
He came clean?

736
00:48:11,201 --> 00:48:12,202
That bastard told her,

737
00:48:12,285 --> 00:48:14,496
"I think I found the love of my life."

738
00:48:14,579 --> 00:48:17,124
He talked some bullshit
and told her he doesn't need

739
00:48:17,207 --> 00:48:18,917
money or custody, just a divorce.

740
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:20,210
Does that even make sense, Nan-suk?

741
00:48:20,293 --> 00:48:22,003
That's a load of bull.
She can't divorce him.

742
00:48:22,087 --> 00:48:24,047
-Of course not.
-Right, it'll only benefit him.

743
00:48:24,715 --> 00:48:26,550
I think I'd let him go.

744
00:48:26,633 --> 00:48:27,634
What?

745
00:48:27,718 --> 00:48:29,010
It's one thing if I didn't know,

746
00:48:29,594 --> 00:48:32,139
but I already know
that he doesn't love me anymore.

747
00:48:32,723 --> 00:48:34,349
How could we live under the same roof?

748
00:48:35,392 --> 00:48:37,811
I think that'd make me more pitiful.

749
00:48:49,698 --> 00:48:50,907
-SHOULD I COME PICK YOU UP?
-IT'S OKAY!

750
00:48:50,991 --> 00:48:52,492
ARE YOU STILL OUT?

751
00:48:57,664 --> 00:49:00,000
I think we took plenty.

752
00:49:00,083 --> 00:49:01,460
I'll edit the best cuts
and send them to you.

753
00:49:03,462 --> 00:49:04,546
Where are you going?

754
00:49:04,629 --> 00:49:06,965
I rented out the whole place
for the shoot.

755
00:49:07,507 --> 00:49:08,842
What about the first birthday ceremony?

756
00:49:08,925 --> 00:49:10,886
I'm sorry. Something urgent came up.

757
00:49:18,977 --> 00:49:21,021
I'll see you at work.

758
00:49:21,104 --> 00:49:22,105
-Thank you for the meal.
-All right.

759
00:49:22,189 --> 00:49:23,523
-Hey, you'd better get home safe.
-Oh goodness.

760
00:49:23,607 --> 00:49:25,734
-Get home safely.
-All right. Wait.

761
00:49:25,817 --> 00:49:27,027
My goodness!

762
00:49:27,778 --> 00:49:29,321
I'll get going too.

763
00:49:29,404 --> 00:49:30,822
Thank you for dinner.

764
00:49:30,906 --> 00:49:31,948
Wait, Ms. Lee!

765
00:49:32,032 --> 00:49:33,784
-Let's share. We're going the same way.
-Oh, okay.

766
00:49:33,867 --> 00:49:34,993
We're off.

767
00:49:43,919 --> 00:49:44,795
What?

768
00:49:44,878 --> 00:49:47,339
Wait, where did everyone go?

769
00:49:47,422 --> 00:49:48,632
They all went home.

770
00:49:48,715 --> 00:49:49,925
Oh no.

771
00:49:50,008 --> 00:49:52,803
They have to eat this.

772
00:49:52,886 --> 00:49:54,304
Why'd you buy so much ice cream?

773
00:49:56,556 --> 00:49:59,100
You're drunk. You were drinking
like there was no tomorrow.

774
00:49:59,184 --> 00:50:01,812
No, I'm not drunk at all.

775
00:50:01,895 --> 00:50:03,355
I can even go for round two.

776
00:50:03,438 --> 00:50:04,272
See?

777
00:50:04,356 --> 00:50:06,817
I'm not the slightest bit drunk right now,

778
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:08,360
and I can prove it.

779
00:50:10,529 --> 00:50:13,532
One, two. Cha, cha, cha.

780
00:50:14,825 --> 00:50:18,245
One, two. Cha, cha, cha.

781
00:50:18,912 --> 00:50:20,413
One, two…

782
00:50:21,164 --> 00:50:23,416
You're the drunk one, Mr. Gong.

783
00:50:23,500 --> 00:50:25,377
We didn't even drink that much.

784
00:50:25,460 --> 00:50:27,379
You're such a lightweight.

785
00:50:27,462 --> 00:50:29,005
-Oh jeez.
-Careful.

786
00:50:29,089 --> 00:50:30,423
Careful.

787
00:50:32,592 --> 00:50:34,261
I'll call Mr. Kim for you.

788
00:50:37,222 --> 00:50:38,431
The clover.

789
00:50:45,230 --> 00:50:46,106
I told you.

790
00:50:46,189 --> 00:50:48,066
It was effective, right?

791
00:50:48,650 --> 00:50:50,944
Holding onto it

792
00:50:51,862 --> 00:50:53,780
helped you win.

793
00:50:57,242 --> 00:50:58,326
Yeah, if you say so.

794
00:51:03,123 --> 00:51:04,666
I think

795
00:51:04,749 --> 00:51:07,836
you're a really great person.

796
00:51:10,005 --> 00:51:12,674
You even lied for my sake.

797
00:51:12,757 --> 00:51:14,718
When did I do that?

798
00:51:14,801 --> 00:51:16,303
I know everything.

799
00:51:20,473 --> 00:51:23,852
-Don't tell me--
-How could I not notice? I'm not an idiot.

800
00:51:23,935 --> 00:51:25,312
Come on.

801
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:29,649
You know everything?

802
00:51:31,026 --> 00:51:31,860
All of it?

803
00:51:31,943 --> 00:51:34,237
-Then do you know your husband is--
-Of course.

804
00:51:34,821 --> 00:51:35,989
I know everything.

805
00:51:38,199 --> 00:51:39,242
Abalone porridge.

806
00:51:39,951 --> 00:51:41,244
Ginger tea.

807
00:51:42,037 --> 00:51:44,205
You got all that for me.

808
00:51:45,290 --> 00:51:48,043
You even lied about
being allergic to abalone.

809
00:51:52,005 --> 00:51:55,008
Even earlier, you made sure to put
all the good food in front of me.

810
00:51:55,091 --> 00:51:57,427
You were worried I'd hurt my head
and covered the table corner.

811
00:51:57,510 --> 00:52:00,180
-But you pretended like it was nothing.
-Hold on.

812
00:52:00,263 --> 00:52:01,556
Seriously!

813
00:52:01,640 --> 00:52:04,142
That was because I…

814
00:52:04,225 --> 00:52:05,644
I know.

815
00:52:06,728 --> 00:52:07,687
You're nice to me

816
00:52:09,522 --> 00:52:12,692
only because I'm a member of your team.

817
00:52:13,985 --> 00:52:15,362
But still…

818
00:52:21,993 --> 00:52:25,121
I find myself being swayed.

819
00:52:28,500 --> 00:52:29,834
You know…

820
00:52:32,003 --> 00:52:33,797
the nicer you are to me,

821
00:52:35,757 --> 00:52:37,968
the happier I am, but it's also hard.

822
00:52:41,513 --> 00:52:44,265
Because I know I don't deserve it.

823
00:52:47,143 --> 00:52:48,436
So…

824
00:52:54,567 --> 00:52:55,944
don't be nice to me.

825
00:52:58,947 --> 00:53:01,449
I'll also promise…

826
00:53:04,536 --> 00:53:06,496
not to be swayed after today.

827
00:54:19,486 --> 00:54:20,612
Chew your food thoroughly.

828
00:54:21,154 --> 00:54:22,030
Good.

829
00:54:22,739 --> 00:54:25,366
Sorry. I saw all the missed calls
from you last night.

830
00:54:25,450 --> 00:54:27,243
I was too drunk to check my phone.

831
00:54:27,327 --> 00:54:28,161
It's fine.

832
00:54:30,914 --> 00:54:32,332
Here you go.

833
00:54:34,250 --> 00:54:36,669
Wow, dried pollack soup.

834
00:54:38,671 --> 00:54:40,048
Have some kimchi too, son.

835
00:54:42,509 --> 00:54:44,135
Man, that hits the spot.

836
00:54:44,803 --> 00:54:46,596
Who brought you home last night?

837
00:54:48,139 --> 00:54:49,182
Last night?

838
00:54:50,433 --> 00:54:51,893
I took a taxi home.

839
00:54:51,976 --> 00:54:54,145
I probably did.

840
00:54:54,229 --> 00:54:56,022
Yeah, I did.

841
00:54:56,856 --> 00:54:59,317
From now on, just call me
if you think you're going to drink a lot.

842
00:54:59,400 --> 00:55:00,401
Okay.

843
00:55:07,492 --> 00:55:08,993
-Jin-hui.
-Oh, thank you.

844
00:55:09,077 --> 00:55:10,578
This is the problem with wine.

845
00:55:10,662 --> 00:55:12,455
It feels like my head is swaying nonstop.

846
00:55:12,539 --> 00:55:14,624
Even my intestines are swaying.
I feel like I'm dying.

847
00:55:14,707 --> 00:55:15,875
Are you okay, Da-rim?

848
00:55:17,085 --> 00:55:18,920
It also feels like I'm swaying…

849
00:55:20,338 --> 00:55:21,673
I find myself being swayed.

850
00:55:22,465 --> 00:55:23,591
Don't be nice to me.

851
00:55:25,802 --> 00:55:26,719
What was that?

852
00:55:28,012 --> 00:55:31,599
Ms. Jang, you'll be in charge of
recruiting people for the tree-planting.

853
00:55:31,683 --> 00:55:32,517
Okay.

854
00:55:32,600 --> 00:55:34,018
Ms. Bae and Ms. Lee,

855
00:55:34,102 --> 00:55:36,479
you'll secure the event venue and request
cooperation from public institutions.

856
00:55:37,147 --> 00:55:40,024
Ms. Go, you can prepare the press release.

857
00:55:40,108 --> 00:55:40,942
Got it.

858
00:55:41,025 --> 00:55:42,527
By the way, where's Mr. Gong?

859
00:55:42,610 --> 00:55:44,362
He's in a meeting
with the CSR team leader.

860
00:55:44,445 --> 00:55:46,614
Considering the scale of the project,

861
00:55:46,698 --> 00:55:48,199
we'll need to collaborate with them.

862
00:55:48,283 --> 00:55:49,701
After always supporting other teams,

863
00:55:49,784 --> 00:55:51,995
we're finally at the receiving end
of support.

864
00:55:52,579 --> 00:55:54,372
That's the power
of being in a lead department.

865
00:55:55,540 --> 00:55:58,042
I guess winning that pitch
wasn't all good.

866
00:55:58,126 --> 00:56:00,753
In the end, we need to do everything
we said we'd do.

867
00:56:01,379 --> 00:56:02,755
I know, right?

868
00:56:02,839 --> 00:56:04,507
I'm happy, but this is hard…

869
00:56:05,300 --> 00:56:06,968
The nicer you are to me,

870
00:56:07,051 --> 00:56:08,803
the happier I am, but it's also hard.

871
00:56:08,887 --> 00:56:11,055
I'll also promise
not to be swayed after today.

872
00:56:15,602 --> 00:56:16,978
-What? What's wrong?
-What is it?

873
00:56:17,061 --> 00:56:18,104
-What?
-Is it a cockroach?

874
00:56:18,188 --> 00:56:19,314
-What?
-Where is it?

875
00:56:21,191 --> 00:56:22,859
Please excuse me.
I need to use the bathroom.

876
00:56:23,651 --> 00:56:24,652
Go ahead.

877
00:56:27,405 --> 00:56:28,781
Could it have been a dream?

878
00:56:30,617 --> 00:56:33,119
Wait, did I mess up?

879
00:56:40,084 --> 00:56:41,628
Excuse me, Mr. Gong.

880
00:56:43,546 --> 00:56:44,547
Yes?

881
00:56:44,631 --> 00:56:46,758
So…

882
00:56:48,968 --> 00:56:50,345
About last night…

883
00:56:51,846 --> 00:56:52,931
Did I…

884
00:56:53,598 --> 00:56:56,100
Did we…

885
00:56:57,936 --> 00:57:00,438
Should I ask this or not?

886
00:57:04,359 --> 00:57:06,277
Did you pay for my taxi fare?

887
00:57:06,861 --> 00:57:08,112
The taxi fare?

888
00:57:08,196 --> 00:57:11,950
Yes, I blacked out last night,
so I don't remember a thing.

889
00:57:12,700 --> 00:57:15,370
I was wondering if you paid for it.

890
00:57:16,579 --> 00:57:17,664
You don't remember?

891
00:57:18,957 --> 00:57:19,791
None of it?

892
00:57:19,874 --> 00:57:21,918
No, I don't remember a single thing.

893
00:57:23,002 --> 00:57:24,420
I see.

894
00:57:26,464 --> 00:57:27,298
I'm sorry.

895
00:57:28,424 --> 00:57:29,801
I don't remember either.

896
00:57:30,969 --> 00:57:32,262
I also blacked out.

897
00:57:32,845 --> 00:57:35,682
You don't remember either?
Not a single thing?

898
00:57:36,683 --> 00:57:37,892
Nothing.

899
00:57:40,144 --> 00:57:43,022
I guess you're a lightweight too.

900
00:57:43,106 --> 00:57:45,525
You should cut down on drinking.

901
00:57:45,608 --> 00:57:47,569
All right, well, have a nice day.

902
00:57:54,576 --> 00:57:55,660
Don't be nice to me.

903
00:57:56,619 --> 00:57:59,956
I'll also promise
not to be swayed after today.

904
00:58:13,344 --> 00:58:17,015
YU TAE-YEONG

905
00:58:23,187 --> 00:58:24,022
Ms. Gong!

906
00:58:24,606 --> 00:58:25,440
Ms. Gong.

907
00:58:26,524 --> 00:58:30,612
I've acquired a hidden card
that'll completely overturn

908
00:58:30,695 --> 00:58:31,946
the results of the presentation.

909
00:58:32,030 --> 00:58:33,281
What hidden card?

910
00:58:33,364 --> 00:58:35,033
Please take a look.

911
00:58:35,742 --> 00:58:37,744
I'm busy enough as it is.

912
00:58:40,496 --> 00:58:42,665
What about it? Who is that?

913
00:58:42,749 --> 00:58:44,208
Take a closer look.

914
00:58:44,292 --> 00:58:46,628
This is Go Da-rim from the Mother TF Team,

915
00:58:46,711 --> 00:58:48,254
and that's Team Leader Gong Ji-hyeok.

916
00:58:48,338 --> 00:58:51,049
A scandalous affair
between a married woman

917
00:58:51,132 --> 00:58:52,800
and the chairman's son.

918
00:58:53,676 --> 00:58:56,054
This should be more than enough

919
00:58:56,137 --> 00:58:58,097
to get rid of the Mother TF Team

920
00:58:58,181 --> 00:59:01,351
and even call off the marriage
with Taeyu C&amp;T!

921
00:59:01,434 --> 00:59:03,311
Wait, but look at this.

922
00:59:03,394 --> 00:59:07,065
You can't really see their faces.
Are you sure it's them?

923
00:59:07,148 --> 00:59:08,232
Hold on.

924
00:59:08,316 --> 00:59:11,402
It has to be Go Da-rim.

925
00:59:11,486 --> 00:59:14,155
That's Go Da-rim and Mr. Gong Ji-hyeok.

926
00:59:14,238 --> 00:59:18,576
Anyhow, my team's youngest saw them
with their own eyes.

927
00:59:19,619 --> 00:59:20,953
So?

928
00:59:21,037 --> 00:59:22,205
Should I release it?

929
00:59:25,083 --> 00:59:27,210
If we're going to release it,
we should do it properly.

930
00:59:29,045 --> 00:59:32,715
Keep an eye on these two
and collect more evidence,

931
00:59:33,758 --> 00:59:35,301
so they can't talk their way out of it.

932
00:59:36,678 --> 00:59:37,553
Concrete evidence.

933
00:59:38,137 --> 00:59:39,263
Understood.

934
00:59:43,101 --> 00:59:46,187
TEAM LEADER GONG JI-HYEOK

935
00:59:57,990 --> 00:59:58,950
What are you up to?

936
01:00:00,243 --> 01:00:01,994
I'm writing up the draft
for the press release.

937
01:00:02,078 --> 01:00:03,329
I just want to work on it a bit more.

938
01:00:04,038 --> 01:00:05,623
Have a good night.

939
01:00:05,707 --> 01:00:07,667
How can it take so long to do this?

940
01:00:11,963 --> 01:00:15,258
This reads more like a list of slogans
than a press release.

941
01:00:16,718 --> 01:00:17,552
Does it?

942
01:00:18,970 --> 01:00:19,804
Excuse me.

943
01:00:21,305 --> 01:00:22,765
Take a look at this online article.

944
01:00:23,266 --> 01:00:26,394
You can see the headline, lead, and body.

945
01:00:27,019 --> 01:00:27,854
Right?

946
01:00:28,813 --> 01:00:30,273
-The content includes
-Yes.

947
01:00:30,356 --> 01:00:33,985
-the who, what, and how.
-The who…

948
01:00:34,068 --> 01:00:35,027
The how.

949
01:00:36,404 --> 01:00:38,406
-And second,
-Yes.

950
01:00:38,489 --> 01:00:41,033
-try combining two or three key terms
-Okay.

951
01:00:41,117 --> 01:00:43,536
from the lead
with some creative expressions.

952
01:00:43,619 --> 01:00:45,163
-Got it.
-Yes.

953
01:00:47,206 --> 01:00:49,500
There should be a file
of past press releases.

954
01:00:50,835 --> 01:00:51,753
Hold on.

955
01:00:52,378 --> 01:00:53,212
Okay.

956
01:01:14,817 --> 01:01:17,028
Da-rim, are you feeling sick?

957
01:01:17,111 --> 01:01:18,154
No.

958
01:01:18,237 --> 01:01:20,031
Look at me.

959
01:01:21,949 --> 01:01:24,535
-Let's get you to a hospital.
-No, I'm really fine.

960
01:01:24,619 --> 01:01:26,370
Don't worry about me.

961
01:01:26,454 --> 01:01:27,997
I just need some medicine.

962
01:01:28,080 --> 01:01:29,165
Just listen to me!

963
01:01:29,707 --> 01:01:31,292
Why are you being stubborn
when you're in pain?

964
01:01:32,752 --> 01:01:35,046
I don't want to trouble you.

965
01:01:36,130 --> 01:01:38,466
I don't think I should do that anymore.

966
01:01:39,383 --> 01:01:40,343
Did you forget?

967
01:01:42,386 --> 01:01:43,930
All your organs are mine.

968
01:01:44,722 --> 01:01:45,932
I'm going to do

969
01:01:46,516 --> 01:01:47,767
whatever I want with them.

970
01:01:48,893 --> 01:01:49,811
So just do as I say.

971
01:02:14,168 --> 01:02:18,381
EMERGENCY ROOM

972
01:02:24,762 --> 01:02:27,098
It's stress-induced stomach cramps.

973
01:02:27,181 --> 01:02:29,517
It appears she's been
under a lot of stress recently.

974
01:02:29,600 --> 01:02:31,060
She should be fine soon,

975
01:02:31,143 --> 01:02:32,812
and she can be discharged
when she wakes up.

976
01:02:32,895 --> 01:02:35,731
We'll see how she does on the prescription
and bring her in for a follow-up.

977
01:02:58,921 --> 01:02:59,797
Yeah.

978
01:03:02,174 --> 01:03:03,342
You're right.

979
01:03:05,928 --> 01:03:07,263
It's because you're my team member.

980
01:03:11,142 --> 01:03:12,602
There's no other reason.

981
01:03:16,022 --> 01:03:17,565
So don't let this sway you…

982
01:03:21,402 --> 01:03:22,486
or trouble you.

983
01:03:46,010 --> 01:03:49,388
SEON-U

984
01:03:52,183 --> 01:03:53,392
But right now,

985
01:03:55,227 --> 01:03:56,604
I want to be the only one…

986
01:03:58,731 --> 01:04:00,024
to protect you.

987
01:04:02,360 --> 01:04:03,361
I want to be…

988
01:04:05,488 --> 01:04:06,822
the only one by your side.

989
01:04:14,956 --> 01:04:16,040
I think…

990
01:04:16,958 --> 01:04:18,167
I've lost my mind.

991
01:04:40,982 --> 01:04:45,903
DYNAMITE KISS

992
01:05:16,017 --> 01:05:20,187
You didn't go home and stayed by my side?

993
01:05:20,271 --> 01:05:21,814
You're being looked out for.

994
01:05:21,897 --> 01:05:23,024
And despite the distance,
the worry remains.

995
01:05:23,107 --> 01:05:24,734
It looks to me like you and Mr. Gong

996
01:05:24,817 --> 01:05:27,486
are more than just a team leader
and a team member.

997
01:05:28,279 --> 01:05:29,196
Go Da-rim!

998
01:05:30,614 --> 01:05:32,533
What do you think you're doing?

999
01:05:35,286 --> 01:05:37,371
Can I get Mr. Gong's address?

1000
01:05:37,455 --> 01:05:39,957
Does your husband know you're here?

1001
01:05:40,041 --> 01:05:43,127
I just thought it could maybe
provide some comfort and strength--

1002
01:05:43,210 --> 01:05:44,879
And people call that an affair.

1003
01:05:44,962 --> 01:05:47,214
I'm not a good person.

1004
01:05:47,798 --> 01:05:49,967
I'm also swayed.

1005
01:05:51,302 --> 01:05:55,973
Subtitle translation by: Justin Kim
